subSection.paragraph:
Most of the syrphid fauna of the Amazonian rainforest region is only known from one or a handful of locations ( Reemer & Ståhls 2013 ; Reemer 2016 ;
Miranda 2014
, 2017 ;
Carvalho-Filho et al . 2019
), but it is not clear if they really have a restricted range or if their apparent rarity reflects the difficulty of sampling much of the isolated and difficult-to-access landscape that is predominant in the region. In this sense, the discovery of the new
Copestylum species
further highlights the rich and unknown biodiversity of the Amazon rainforest suggesting also a high probability that more species might be discovered in this fragile, threatened, and unique ecosystem.
